Privacy Policy

Last updated: May 27, 2024

Introduction

Welcome to DISS, an app created by Benjamin Frank ("we," "us," or "our"). Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app, DISS.

1. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personal data from users of the DISS app. The only information we access is the Advertising Identifier (AD ID) to display personalized ads.

2. Use of Collected Information

Advertising: We use the AD ID solely to show personalized ads to our users. This helps us to provide a free app while offering relevant advertisements.
3. Data Sharing

We do not share, sell, or distribute any personal data to third parties. The AD ID is used by our advertising partners to serve personalized ads, but no other data is collected or shared.

4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies

We do not use cookies or any other tracking technologies in the DISS app.

5. Data Security

We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. Although we do not collect or store any personal data, we take reasonable steps to protect the AD ID from unauthorized access or disclosure.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: pb-code+privacy@outlook.com
Name: Benjamin Frank

8. Conclusion

Thank you for using DISS. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. By using our app, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

